# <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, chore, perf, ci, build
# Scope: optional module like cli, runtime, docs, tracking
# Summary: imperative mood, <= 72 chars (e.g., "restructure CLI subcommands")
#
# Why:
# - What user/problem is being solved?
#
# What changed:
# - Key change 1
# - Key change 2
#
# Notes:
# - Any migration, compatibility, or follow-up details
#
# Example:
# refactor(cli): restructure command parsing with subcommands
#
# Why:
# - Eliminate ambiguous argument parsing for usage commands
#
# What changed:
# - Added professor-first command hierarchy
# - Introduced usage/translate/transcribe subcommands
#
# Notes:
# - --list-models and --update-pricing remain global commands
